SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1100
By Roberts
A RESOLUTION to honor and celebrate the 100th anniversary of
J. I. Baldwin and Son Barbecue in Springfield.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to honor those
outstanding restaurants that have earned the loyalty and accolades of Tennesseans through
their mouth-watering cuisine; and
WHEREAS, Middle Tennessee is, without a doubt, home to some of the best barbeque
restaurants in the world, and J. I. Baldwin and Son Barbecue in Springfield is certainly one of
them; and
WHEREAS, founded in 1926, J. I. Baldwin and Son Barbecue has literally served
millions of pounds of barbeque to hungry, but ultimately satisfied, customers during the past 100
years; and
WHEREAS, J. I. Baldwin and Son Barbecue is renowned among its customers for
serving the world's best barbecue while providing excellent customer service; and
WHEREAS, it is only appropriate that we should pay tribute to J. I. Baldwin and Son
Barbecue's longstanding commitment to great food and great service as its owners and
employees usher the restaurant into its second century of operation; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and celebrate the 100th anniversary of J. I.
Baldwin and Son Barbecue in Springfield and extend to its owners and employees our best
wishes for much-continued success in serving delicious barbeque to the people during the next
100 years.
